By: Representative Werkheiser of the 157th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Darin McCoy on his outstanding public service; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Darin McCoy is an active member of the Georgia Council of Probate Judges,
4 where he has held every office in the state organization, including president from 2002 to
5 2003, and currently severs as Secretary-Treasurer; and
6 WHEREAS, he served as the 2016 President of the Constitutional Officers of Georgia, which
7 is composed of all of Georgia's Sheriffs, Superior Court Clerks, Tax Commissioners, and
8 Probate Judges; and
9 WHEREAS, he has served as an instructor for the University of Georgia's Institute of
10 Continuing Judicial Education, instructing classes for Probate Court Clerks and Probate
11 Court Judges across the state; and
12 WHEREAS, upon completing his current term in 2028, he will has served 36 years in office.
13 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
14 the members of this body recognize and commend Darin McCoy for his efficient, effective,
